# IX Title Actions — parent actions vs. overflow

Toolinator's title-actions template already handles overflow for you: the first three actions render inline and the rest collapse into a `DropdownFlyout` with a caret. You do **not** need to build the overflow yourself.

## Legitimate use of a parent action (grouped sub-actions)

Use `{ title, children: [...] }` only when the sub-actions are **semantically a single grouped action** that a user naturally thinks of as one control:

- `Export → PDF / CSV / Excel`
- `Download → PDF / original / zipped`
- `Share → Copy link / Email / Slack`

Each of these has a named parent verb that groups variants. The parent action title is the verb (`Export`, `Download`, `Share`) and renders as a button with a caret beside it — the caret is correct because the user picks which variant to run.

## Anti-pattern — do NOT use a parent action as a fake kebab menu

**Never** do this:

```tsx
// WRONG — fake kebab menu
{
  title: ' ',                    // blank or whitespace title
  icon: <EllipsisVertical />,    // "more" icon
  children: [
    { title: 'Project Hub', view: 'hub' },
    { title: 'Home', view: 'home' },
    { title: 'New tool', view: 'list' },
  ],
}
```

Two things go wrong with this pattern:

1. **`@procore/core-react` treats any defined `label` (including `''`) as "show caret"** — so the kebab renders with a stray caret beside the ellipsis icon. That bug was fixed on `feat/core-title-overflow-tool-landing` (branch trim to label-only `Dropdown` fix) but the pattern itself still produces an IX-non-compliant trigger.
2. **It reinvents Toolinator's built-in overflow.** Consumers should not manage which actions go inline vs. which go to the overflow — Toolinator owns that decision.

### Fix: flatten the children into top-level actions

```tsx
// RIGHT — let Toolinator handle overflow
actions: [
  { title: 'Action [Item name]', variant: 'primary' },
  { title: 'Edit' },
  { title: 'Export', children: [{ title: 'CSV' }, { title: 'PDF' }] }, // legitimate parent
  { title: 'Project Hub', view: 'hub' },
  { title: 'Home', view: 'home' },
  { title: 'New tool', view: 'list' },
]
```

With 6 actions, Toolinator renders the first 3 inline (`Action`, `Edit`, `Export`) and collapses the remaining 3 (`Project Hub`, `Home`, `New tool`) into the overflow flyout automatically.

## Overflow threshold

The threshold is hardcoded at 3 today. Configurable per layout (`titleActionsVisibleMax`) is a **Toolinator proposal** — see [`TOOLINATOR-EXTENSIONS.md`](../../skills/ds-cheat-sheet/TOOLINATOR-EXTENSIONS.md). Until it lands, do not try to work around the 3 by injecting a custom kebab parent action — rely on the built-in overflow.

## Quick checklist

- Is the parent action a **verb that groups variants** (`Export`, `Download`, `Share`)? → `children` is legitimate.
- Is the parent action an **ellipsis icon with a blank / whitespace title**? → Anti-pattern. Flatten the children into top-level actions.
- Is the children list a set of **unrelated destinations or commands**? → Flatten. These should be separate top-level actions and let Toolinator overflow them.

## Scope

This rule applies to **Toolinator action configs** (`layout.actions`, feature `actions`). It does NOT apply to raw `@procore/core-react` `Button`, `Dropdown`, or `IxQuickPopover` composition inside custom UI — those are separate primitives with their own IX rules (see `ix-popover.mdc`).

